        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 7 at 3:42AM CDT until June 7 at 4:30AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southeastern Oldham County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Southwestern Potter County in the Panhandle of Texas...

* Until 430 AM CDT.

* At 341 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 4 miles northwest
of Vega, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.
Hail damage to vehicles is expected.

* Locations impacted include...
Vega, Wildorado, Valley De Oro, and Amarillo.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
